## Video 19 - Design Patterns

- Recommended Book: Design Patterns - Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software

__The Singleton Pattern__

- A pattern that restricts classes to only being instantiated once during the execution of the program

- Database Connections, config values, constants vars, etc.

- __ class instance variable - "__" makes python recognize it as private
- Static method - allows to call class method before an instance of the class is even instatiated

__The Observer Pattern__

- When dependent objects are updated or notified by one or more subject objects

- Popular in UI's (event driven responses)

- 2 classes defined by this pattern

- Subject, which maintains a list of observers & includes methods for attaching, detaching, notifying observers
- Observer, which has a method to receive the updates from subject

Model View Controller

- Model - the component that stores data Database/data source
- View - the component that displays the data
- Controller - Handles logic flow, user interactions, direct models & views
